|f \ast g(x)| \le \int_{\mathbf R^n} |f(y)| |g(x-y)| \, dy \le ||g||_\infty \int_{\mathbf R^n} |f(y)| \, dy = ||f||_1 ||g||_\infty
|f\ast g(x) - f\ast g(z)| = \left| \int_{\mathbf R^n} \left( f(y-x) - f(y-z) \right) g(y) \, dy \right| \le ||g||_\infty \int_{\mathbf R^n} |f(y-x) - f(y-z)| \, dy.
|x-z| \to 0
L^1
